.Dd June 26, 2026
.Dt GIT-MFC 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm "git mfc"
.Nd cherry-pick commits from an upstream branch to a stable or release branch
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl efn
.Op Fl -ignore-reverts
.Op Fl -origin Ar branch
.Op Fl r Ar remote
.Ar revision ...
.Nm
.Fl -pending
.Op Fl a Ar author
.Op Fl -all
.Op Fl -baking
.Op Fl -origin Ar branch
.Op Fl r Ar remote
.Nm
.Fl -dangling
.Op Fl a Ar author
.Op Fl -all
.Op Fl -origin Ar branch
.Op Fl r Ar remote
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility helps with MFCing (merge from CURRENT) commits to
.Fx
stable and release branches.
It must be run from a checkout of the branch being MFCed
.Em to .
The origin branch is determined automatically and can be
overridden with the
.Fl -origin
option.
.Pp
There are three modes of operation:
.Bl -enum
.It
In the default mode, one or more revisions are specified on the command line.
Each revision is cherry-picked with
.Fl x
to the current branch.
The origin branch is scanned for commits with
.Dq Fixes: ,
.Dq MFC-with: ,
or
.Dq MFC with:
tags referencing any of the specified revisions, and those fixup commits
are automatically included in the correct order.
.Pp
If a specified revision has been reverted on the origin branch,
.Nm
refuses to cherry-pick it unless
.Fl -ignore-reverts
is given.
Fixup commits that have been reverted are skipped with a warning.
.Pp
Commits that have already been cherry-picked to the current branch are
automatically skipped.
This allows the same
.Nm
command to be re-run after resolving a conflict without re-applying
earlier commits.
Use
.Fl f
to override this behavior.
.It
In
.Fl -pending
mode, no revisions are specified.
Instead,
.Nm
scans the origin branch for commits with
.Dq MFC after:
tags whose waiting period has elapsed and which have not already been
cherry-picked to the current branch.
Commits that have been reverted upstream are excluded.
By default, only commits authored by the current user
.Pq as determined by Xr git-config 1
are shown.
.It
In
.Fl -dangling
mode, no revisions are specified.
Instead,
.Nm
finds commits in the current branch that have been cherry-picked from the
origin branch but are missing associated fixup commits.
Fixup commits that have been reverted upstream are excluded.
By default, only cherry-picks authored by the current user
.Pq as determined by Xr git-config 1
are considered.
.El
.Pp
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width "-a author"
.It Fl a Ar author , Fl -author Ar author
With
.Fl -pending
or
.Fl -dangling ,
filter results to commits whose author email contains the given string.
By default, the value of
.Va user.email
from
.Xr git-config 1
is used.
.It Fl -all
With
.Fl -pending
or
.Fl -dangling ,
show commits from all authors instead of only the current user.
.It Fl -dangling
Find cherry-picked commits in the current branch that are missing fixup
commits from the origin branch.
Cannot be combined with
.Fl -pending
or revision arguments.
.It Fl e , Fl -edit
Open the commit message in an editor before committing each cherry-pick.
Passed through to
.Xr git-cherry-pick 1 .
.It Fl f , Fl -force
Cherry-pick commits even if they appear to have already been cherry-picked
to the current branch.
By default,
.Nm
skips commits that are already present.
.It Fl -ignore-reverts
Cherry-pick commits even if they have been reverted on the origin branch.
Without this flag,
.Nm
exits with an error when a reverted commit is specified.
.It Fl -baking
With
.Fl -pending ,
also show commits whose
.Dq MFC after:
waiting period has not yet elapsed.
These are annotated with the date they become ready.
.It Fl n
Dry run.
List the commits that would be cherry-picked, but do not actually
cherry-pick them.
The remote is not fetched in this mode.
.It Fl -origin Ar branch
Specify the upstream branch name.
The default is determined automatically from
.Pa sys/conf/newvers.sh :
.Dq main
for STABLE branches and
.Dq stable/ Ns Ar major
for RELEASE branches.
.It Fl -pending
Show upstream commits with
.Dq MFC after:
tags that are ready to be cherry-picked.
Cannot be combined with
.Fl -dangling
or revision arguments.
.It Fl r Ar remote , Fl -remote Ar remote
Specify the git remote to fetch from.
The default is the currently checked-out branch's upstream remote.
.El
.Pp
Before running any operation,
.Nm
ensures that the origin is up to date by fetching it from the specified remote.
.Sh IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
.Nm
is implemented in Python and depends on the gitpython module.
.Pp
.Nm
uses text strings in commit log messages to establish relationships between
commits.
It recognizes the following tags in commit log messages:
.Bl -tag -width "MFC after:"
.It Dq Fixes: Ar hash
Indicates that this commit fixes the commit identified by
.Ar hash .
When MFCing the referenced commit,
.Nm
will automatically include this fixup commit.
.It Dq MFC-with: Ar hash , Dq MFC with: Ar hash
Equivalent to
.Dq Fixes: ;
indicates that this commit should be MFCed together with the referenced commit.
.It Dq MFC after: Ar N Ar unit
Indicates that this commit should be MFCed after the specified waiting period.
Recognized units are
.Dq day ,
.Dq days ,
.Dq week ,
.Dq weeks ,
.Dq month ,
and
.Dq months .
Used by the
.Fl -pending
mode.
.El
.Pp
.Nm
also looks for strings of the form,
.Dq This reverts commit Ar hash ,
inserted by
.Xr git-revert 1 ,
and
.Dq cherry picked from commit Ar hash ,
inserted by
.Xr git-cherry-pick 1 .
.Sh EXAMPLES
Cherry-pick a single commit to the current branch, automatically including
any fixup commits:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ git mfc abc123
.Ed
.Pp
Cherry-pick a range of commits:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ git mfc abc123~..def456
.Ed
.Pp
Preview which commits would be cherry-picked without actually doing it:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ git mfc -n abc123
.Ed
.Pp
Cherry-pick a commit, opening an editor to amend the commit message first:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ git mfc -e abc123
.Ed
.Pp
List your commits that are ready for MFC:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ git mfc --pending
.Ed
.Pp
List pending commits from all authors:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ git mfc --pending --all
.Ed
.Pp
Include commits whose MFC-after period has not yet elapsed:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ git mfc --pending --baking
.Ed
.Pp
List commits ready for MFC by a specific author:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ git mfc --pending -a markj@FreeBSD.org
.Ed
.Pp
Find MFCs in the current branch that are missing fixup commits:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ git mfc --dangling
.Ed
.Pp
Cherry-pick a commit that was reverted upstream:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ git mfc --ignore-reverts abc123
.Ed
.Pp
Use a different remote and origin branch:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ git mfc -r freebsd --origin main abc123
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr git-cherry-pick 1 ,
.Xr git-config 1 ,
.Xr git-revert 1 ,
.Xr development 7
.Sh AUTHORS
The
.Nm
utility was written by
